The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Laxman may be dropped

St Kitts: The axe might fall on middle-order batsman VVS Laxman as India wriggle out of the holiday mode to concentrate on selection matters for the third Test against the West Indies starting here Thursday. 

The Indians might have dominated the West Indies in the first two Tests but the fact remains that they have not been able to force a victory. 

National selector VB Chandrashekhar stoked the debate with the observation that a third spinner is the need of the hour, which is a sign of changing times as Harbhajan Singh is now seen as a third option after Anil Kumble and Virender Sehwag . (PTI) 




